_evidence.text: additively manufactured using a mixture of pure Ti, Hf, Nb, and V powders (all with purities exceeding 99.95 %)
tensile tests were conducted on the as-deposited samples at various temperatures, including RT, 673 K, 773 K, 873 K, and 1073 K, at a strain rate of 1 × 10−3 s−1
remelting procedure to fabricate the T42 RHEA
yield strength of the as-fabricated T42 alloy decreased to ~681 MPa

lattice constant of the T42 alloy was determined to be 3.3176 Å
